The paper deals with designing a new succinct data structure for the rank problem, which is a fundamental problem in data structures. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category. The paper also involves techniques from information theory (cs.IT), computational geometry (cs.CG), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM) to establish connections and prove results. Additionally, the paper discusses the space-time tradeoff, which is a common topic in the field of succinct data structures and falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
